Aorus has revealed its latest gaming laptop based on Nvidia’s Max-Q design technology at Computex 2017. The Aorus X5 MD is a 22.9mm-thick laptop which boasts an Nvidia GeForce GTX 1080 graphics card paired with an Intel Core i7-7820HK processor. The device features a 4K display and support for Nvidia’s Ansel, VRWorks, and G-Sync technologies. Aorus has equipped the X5 MD with its RGB Fusion keyboard and an advanced cooling system, which consists of six heat pipes, four exhaust vents, and two fans. The device is set to launch later this year, but no pricing was announced.